status: Lucknow Super Giants won by 28 runs

videos.headline: Naveen-ul-Haq to Siraj, out Caught by Pooran!! First time a team has been bowled out in IPL 2024! Slow, full and in the slot at 103.1kph, Siraj looks to loft it downtown. Decent contact but Pooran takes a superb catch. Sprints to his left from long-on and dives across to take a tumbling catch. LSG win by 28 runs. Siraj c Pooran b Naveen-ul-Haq 12(8) [6s-2]

Yash Thakur to Lomror, out Caught by Pooran!! Gone now! This should be the killer blow. 141.7kph, full outside off, Lomror clears his front leg to thump it over wide long-off. Doesn't get the necessary elevation and Pooran moves to his right to reverse-cup it. Not the most convincing catch but he manages to hold onto it with his left hand. Lomror c Pooran b Yash Thakur 33(13) [4s-3 6s-3]

Yash Thakur to Lomror, out Mayank Dagar Run Out!! 1 run completed. 125.3kph, pace off, Lomror loses his shape as he tries to launch it downtown. Ends up slicing it in the air and fortunately for him, Pooran fails to spot it ceanly and the ball falls short of him at long-on. However, Mayank Dagar eyes a second and tumbles into the ground as he turns back on being sent back. Pooran scores a direct-hit with a bullet throw at the keeper's end from long-on and poor Dagar was nowhere in the frame. Mayank Dagar run out (Pooran) 0(1)

Naveen-ul-Haq to Karthik, out Caught by Rahul!! Naveen-ul-Haq silences the Chinnaswamy crowd. Slower ball into the wicket, Karthik shuffles across to pull it towards fine leg. He is early into his pull and the ball lobs up towards the keeper off the batsman's glove. A sitter for KL Rahul who acceps the gift gleefully. Karthik c Rahul b Naveen-ul-Haq 4(8)

Mayank Yadav to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Padikkal!! Third wicket for Mayank Yadav! Another batter perishes playing the pull shot. No control of this stroke. The line is outside off as Mayank bowls short and Patidar goes through with his pull shot and only manages to get a top-edge. Padikkal, at deep backward square leg, waits under the swirling ball to take it safely. Rajat Patidar c Padikkal b Mayank Yadav 29(21) [4s-2 6s-2]

Mayank Yadav to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Padikkal!! Third wicket for Mayank Yadav! Another batter perishes playing the pull shot. No control of this stroke. The line is outside off as Mayank bowls short and Patidar goes through with his pull shot and only manages to get a top-edge. Padikkal, at deep backward square leg, waits under the swirling ball to take it safely. Rajat Patidar c Padikkal b Mayank Yadav 29(21) [4s-2 6s-2]

Stoinis to Anuj Rawat, out Caught by Padikkal!! 131.9kph, once again Anuj Rawat skips down the track. This time Stoinis doesn't err. Bowls the bouncer and the length is spot-on. Gets big on the batter who pulls awkwardly. Hits him high on the bat and Padikkal comes in from mid-on to take another catch. Stoinis does a little jog as RCB lose half their side. Anuj Rawat c Padikkal b Stoinis 11(21)

Mayank Yadav to Green, out Bowled!! WOW! This is top quality pace bowling. Pacy short of a good length ball, nips in a bit and Green ends up playing down the wrong line. Green stays leg-side and his feet is cemented. The ball beats the outside edge to hit the top of off. This kid is special! Mayank Yadav is rightly pumped up. RCB in a spot of bother. Green b Mayank Yadav 9(9) [4s-1]

Mayank Yadav to Maxwell, out Caught by Pooran!! There's Mayank and his pace. He accounted for three Punjab batters in the same way and Maxwell is his latest victim. 151ks short of length delivery and Maxwell is rushed on the pull, the ball hits the higher part of the bat and balloons in front of mid-on, Pooran runs in and completes the dolly. Maxwell woeful start with the bat this season extends to another game. RCB are in trouble. Maxwell c Pooran b Mayank Yadav 0(2)

Mayank Yadav to du Plessis, out du Plessis Run Out!! Wow! Brilliant work from Padikkal. Both openers sent back in succession and LSG are cock-a-hoop. Angled in and Faf turns it to mid-wicket, straight to Padikkal and he sets off on a non-existent single, Padikkal gets a good bounce to gather the ball and then has one stump to aim, he hits the target and Faf is not even in the frame. du Plessis run out (Padikkal) 19(13) [4s-3]

Mayank Yadav to du Plessis, out du Plessis Run Out!! Wow! Brilliant work from Padikkal. Both openers sent back in succession and LSG are cock-a-hoop. Angled in and Faf turns it to mid-wicket, straight to Padikkal and he sets off on a non-existent single, Padikkal gets a good bounce to gather the ball and then has one stump to aim, he hits the target and Faf is not even in the frame. du Plessis run out (Padikkal) 19(13) [4s-3]

M Siddharth to Kohli, out Caught by Padikkal!! The TN spinner is off on a celebratory run. It is his maiden IPL wicket and it is the big one of Kohli. Why wouldn't you be elated? This is a massive breakthrough for LSG in the powerplay as Kohli has been RCB's go-to batter this season. This was bowled smartly. Slowed it up and drew Kohli into the big shot, the ball turned away and caught the outer half, the ball skies to backward point and Padikkal back tracks a few steps to take the catch. Kohli c Padikkal b M Siddharth 22(16) [4s-2 6s-1]

Yash Dayal to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by du Plessis!! That's an excellent catch by Faf. Maxwell dropped a similar one early in the game and he's the first one there to embrace Faf. Slower ball banged into the surface, Badoni fetches it from outside off and toe-ends the slap over extra cover, Faf runs back and puts in the dive to hang on. He went with both hands and ensured he had the ball in control even after hitting the ground. Ayush Badoni c du Plessis b Yash Dayal 0(3)

Topley to de Kock, out Caught by Mayank Dagar!! Should have been two in two. But RCB will settle with the set batter walking back. de Kock would be livid with himself. This was a juicy full toss outside off, de Kock gets no timing or the middle as he looks to loft down the ground, in fact the bat turns on impact and the miscue is held near long-off. Not a fluent knock but he kept picking the boundaries when needed. de Kock c Mayank Dagar b Topley 81(56) [4s-8 6s-5]

Maxwell to Stoinis, out Caught by Mayank Dagar!! Second wicket for Maxwell. And once again it is the right hander he accounts for. Stoinis is disappointed as he starts the walk back. This was the half tracker and he wanted to smash it out of the ground, once more the ball bounces a tad more and he ends up slicing it over point, Dagar runs back from backward point and takes a good catch. Stoinis c Mayank Dagar b Maxwell 24(15) [4s-1 6s-2]

Siraj to Padikkal, out Caught by Anuj Rawat!! This is what they were trying to do all day. To bowl short at the LHBs and make them fetch the pull shot for a top edge, finally it's paid off, thanks to a brilliant catch running back by the keeper. Give this to the fielder I say. Short delivery angling across, Padikkal looks to pull, big top edge that only has height, keeper runs back, third man runs in, keeper says mine and somehow clings on with both hands and makes it look simple. DDP's poor start to the IPL continues. Padikkal c Anuj Rawat b Siraj 6(11)

Maxwell to Rahul, out Caught by Mayank Dagar!! Mistimed high and taken at cover. This is a massive wicket for RCB. They brought on Maxi to get Quinton but they have got the big fish. KL tried to maximize on a short ball, but this seems to have jumped extra and the pull shot was a complete mishit. RCB fans find their voices again. Actually was rushed on the shot a bit. Rahul c Mayank Dagar b Maxwell 20(14) [6s-2]
